asi-spherical shape imposed by\nthe large surface energy, to more deformed shapes only controlled by the\nbending energy, is observed numerically at $\\hat \\sigma_{\\rm eff}\\simeq 0$. We\npropose that the buckling transition, observed for planar supported membranes\nin the literature, occurs for $\\hat \\sigma_{\\rm eff}\\simeq-1$, the associated\nnegative frame tension playing the role of a compressive force.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 28 Jun 2017 20:31:08 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 4 Sep 2017 13:10:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-09-05"}
